The paper deals with secret-key agreement over wireless channels, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of block-fading channels and channel estimation also suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and networking (cs.NI) sub-categories. Finally, the emphasis on practical implementation and the need for randomness-sharing may indicate a link to systems and control (cs.SI) sub-category.
